  "title": "Quality improvements not reflected in CPI",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following is an example of how the consumer price index <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, C P I, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, C P I, close parenthesis\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mo>(</mo><mtext>C</mtext><mtext>P</mtext><mtext>I</mtext><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> exhibits bias in its estimates of changes in the cost of living?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Energy prices have a higher impact on inflation than other input costs do.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">New products are always overrepresented in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C P I\"><math alttext=\"C P I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>C</mtext><mtext>PI</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C P I\"><math alttext=\"C P I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>C</mtext><mtext>PI</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> assigns greater weight to measures of welfare than it does to economic activity.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Product improvements are not always fully reflected in the calculation of the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C P I\"><math alttext=\"C P I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>C</mtext><mtext>PI</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C P I\"><math alttext=\"C P I\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>C</mtext><mtext>PI</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> adjusts for the substitution of less expensive goods by consumers.</p>",
        "value": "i5"
      }
    ]
  },
